{{Infobox company | name = Libramatic | logo = | owner = BitBaboon | foundation = July, 2012 | genre = [[Integrated library system]] | website = [http://www.libramatic.com/ libramatic.com] }}
'''Libramatic''' is a cloud-based library management [[software as a service|service provider]] based in [[Dublin]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]
Libramatic allows [[librarian]]s to catalog library inventory by scanning an [[ISBN]] using a [[smartphone]]'s camera or by using a [[Barcode scanner|USB barcode scanner]] on a [[personal computer]].
Libramatic officially launched in July 2012 at a startup event in Dublin.<ref>{{cite news|first=SiliconRepublic|title=Twelve-year-old entrepreneur wins crowds over at Dublin Beta start-up gathering|url=http://www.siliconrepublic.com/start-ups/item/28613-twelve-year-old-entrepreneu|accessdate=8 December 2013|newspaper=SiliconRepublic|date=2012-07-31}}</ref>
By utilising a correlation of multiple online data sources,<ref>{{cite web|first=Libramatic|title=Libramatic Product Description|url=http://libramatic.com/product/|publisher=Libramatic|accessdate=8 December 2013}}</ref> it searches for information on that book using an undisclosed algorithm and stores it allowing librarians to circulate books based on an [[ISBN]].
The use of online library management systems has increased drastically since the rise of "[[Cloud computing|cloud]]" technology. Many modern cloud-based solutions now allow automated cataloging by scanning a book's ISBN. This technology was pioneered by Libramatic, although it is currently in use by systems such as [[LibraryWorld]].
