ea (British Army officer)|George Lea]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=45776|page=10843|date=12 September 1972}}</ref> * 1 November 1975: Sir [[Napier Crookenden]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=46729|page=13893|date=4 November 1975}}</ref> * 1 November 1981: Sir [[Terence Douglas Herbert McMeekin]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=48784|page=13989|date=4 November 1981}}</ref> * 1 March 1983: Sir [[Hugh Patrick Cunningham]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=49281|page=3121|date=4 March 1983}}</ref> * 1 March 1986: Sir [[Peter Hudson (British Army officer)|Peter Hudson]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=50449|page=3199|date=6 March 1986}}</ref> * 1 March 1989: Sir [[Derek Boorman]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=51663|page=2755|date=6 March 1989}}</ref> * 1 March 1992: Sir [[Robert Francis Richardson]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=52851|page=3801|date=3 March 1992}}</ref> * 1 March 1995: Sir [[Michael Stuart Gray]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=53975|page=3593|date=7 March 1995}}</ref> * 1 March 1998: Sir [[Anthony Arthur Denison-Smith]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=55059|page=2517|date=4 March 1998}}</ref> * 1 March 2001: Sir [[Roderick Alexander Cordy-Simpson]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=56136|page=2634|date=2 March 2001}}</ref> * 1 March 2004: Sir [[Hew William Royston Pike]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=57221|page=2671|date=2 March 2004}}</ref> * 1 March 2007: Sir [[Cedric Norman George Delves]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=58265|page=3241|date=6 March 2007}}</ref> * 4 May 2010: [[Peter Thomas Clayton Pearson]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=59411|page=8081|date=5 May 2010}}</ref> * 25 February 2015: Sir [[Simon Vincent Mayall]]<ref>{{London Gazette|nolink=y|issue=61158|page=3810|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> }} ===Deputy Lieutenants=== {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| * 1709: James Pendlebury<ref name=Williamson>John Charles Fox ed., ''The Official Diary of Lieutenant-General Adam Williamson, Deputy-